The paper discusses parallel algorithms for learning distributed representations in large-scale knowledge repositories, which is a common topic in machine learning and data management. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DB (Databases) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of MapReduce programming model, which is a distributed computing framework, indicating that it may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on several well-known knowledge bases, suggesting that it may fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
